                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.466,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kagan has the opinion of the court this morning in Case 13-1019, Mach Mining v EEOC."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.466,
                        "stop": 269.662,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15094,
                            "name": "Elena Kagan",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/elena_kagan",
                            "last_name": "Kagan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2738,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1281157200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Barack Obama",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2738"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32690,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44456,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/elena-kagan-photo_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 1931,
                            "identifier": "elena_kagan"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.466,
                                "stop": 19.041,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Title VII charges the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission or EEOC with enforcing the laws and prohibitions against discrimination in the workplace."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.041,
                                "stop": 35.512,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "One of those provisions states that before the EEOC may sue an employer for discrimination, it must try through what are called informal methods of conference, conciliation and persuasion to get the employer to voluntarily comply with the law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.512,
                                "stop": 41.338,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Only if that attempts to conciliate the claim fails may the EEOC file a suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.338,
                                "stop": 50.96,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case is about whether and to what extent Courts may review and enforce the EEOC\u0027s efforts to achieve voluntary compliance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.96,
                                "stop": 60.148,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In the case the EEOC found that petitioner Mach Mining might well have discriminated against a class of women by failing to hire them as coalminers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.148,
                                "stop": 67.981,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Commission sent a letter to Mach Mining saying as much and letting the company know that someone would be in touch to try to conciliate the claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.981,
                                "stop": 78.376,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We don\u0027t know what happened after that, the record doesn\u0027t say, but about a year later the EEOC sent another letter to Mach Mining saying its conciliation efforts had failed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.376,
                                "stop": 81.338,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The EEOC then sued the company."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.338,
                                "stop": 90.161,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As a defense to the suit, Mach Mining alleged that the EEOC hadn\u0027t met its duty under Title VII to conciliate the claim before filing suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 90.161,
                                "stop": 96.205,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The EEOC countered that its conciliation efforts weren\u0027t subject to judicial review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.205,
                                "stop": 105.68,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That means a Court would have no power to determine whether the EEOC complied with its statutory obligation to try to conciliate claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.68,
                                "stop": 112.616,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit agreed that the EEOC\u0027s conciliation efforts are unreviewable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.616,
                                "stop": 115.927,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Today, we hold that the Seventh Circuit was wrong."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.927,
                                "stop": 120.302,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The EEOC\u0027s statutory duty is subject to judicial review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.302,
                                "stop": 132.271,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But we also hold that the scope of that review is narrow, reflecting the wide discretion Title VII gives the EEOC to decide how to conduct its informal discussions with employers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 132.271,
                                "stop": 138.629,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As to the first point, this Court presumes that Congress intends for Courts to review agency action."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.629,
                                "stop": 143.385,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When Congress directs an agency to do a thing, it wants that thing to get done."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.385,
                                "stop": 146.282,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Judicial review helps make sure that happens."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.282,
                                "stop": 148.536,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This is just a commonsense idea."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.536,
                                "stop": 153.808,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When an agency knows a Court is checking on it, the agency will be more careful."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.808,
                                "stop": 159.162,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The presumption in favor of judicial review can be overcome, but nothing does so here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.162,
                                "stop": 166.079,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Congress used mandatory language to describe the EEOC\u0027s duty to try to achieve voluntary compliance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.079,
                                "stop": 179.615,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "According to the statute, the EEOC must prior to filing any suit give the employer notice of what the charge is and must provide the employer with an opportunity to discuss and try to resolve the matter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.615,
                                "stop": 188.423,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Courts routinely enforce similar compulsory prerequisites to suit in Title VII litigation and nothing is different about this one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 188.423,
                                "stop": 193.805,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "At the same time our opinion makes clear that the scope of this judicial review is narrow."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.805,
                                "stop": 207.711,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The statute, as I just said, requires the EEOC to tell the employer about the claim and give the employer a chance to settle it, but the statute leaves entirely to the EEOC how to conduct those discussions and when to end them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.711,
                                "stop": 217.25,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It sets no rules of negotiation and it makes the EEOC the sole arbiter of when the employer has offered enough to stave off a lawsuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 217.25,
                                "stop": 228.419,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The statute also contains a strict confidentiality provision, preventing the disclosure in a future suit of anything that happened during conciliation discussions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 228.419,
                                "stop": 239.085,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That statutory framework makes clear that a Court is not to delve into the content of the discussions between the EEOC and the employer about a discrimination charge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 239.085,
                                "stop": 248.685,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Rather, the Court is to perform the relatively barebones task of making sure that proper notice of the claim was given and that those discussions occurred."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 248.685,
                                "stop": 265.708,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That kind of review ensures that the EEOC complies with the law, while respecting the broad discretion Congress gave the EEOC to conduct conciliation discussions in the way it thinks will best promote the goal of eliminating workplace discrimination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 265.708,
                                "stop": 269.662,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
